(Kage)<br>
Kage could feel exactly what was going on, because he was pulling at some of her energy too. 'Why waste a perfectly good time to test her control?' his healing was sped up a bit, but nothing extreme. 'She's very good with control, when she feels she has to be.' He looked down at the now half way healed wound. 'Unforunatly, she still needs some lessons on focas. Using her hands? How old fashioned.' He climbed into the window in the attic. 'No reason to let them be alone for long...' he got back into his Kurt getup and started walking down the hallway to their room. He knocked on Enderla's door. &quot;Is everything alright in there? Sir? Miss? You are alright, aren't you?&quot; He smirked quietly. 'Cause if Enderla isn't, she might need medical help, and we don't want her to have any records here to prove that she went missing when she leaves...' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=animagess@collisionworld>Animagess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 327<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/2/03 2:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: nervous?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Crow shook his head, trying to get his mind clear as soon as possible.  No sense in having the 3i re-energized if he couldn't use its advantage.  He stood over Derla, who had fainted on the bed; he was about to check her pulse when someone rapped on the door.<br>
<br>
Turning, Crow heard Kurt's voice coming through the door.  &quot;Is everything alright in there? Sir? Miss? You are alright, aren't you?&quot; <br>
<br>
At that moment, the 3i seemed to spark with an unknown energy.  It burst open, and Crow felt an intense pain shooting through his forehead.<br>
<br>
Gasping, Crow leaned part of his weight on the synteshart as the 3i began to speak.  Trying to ignore the flashes of fire streaming through his head, Crow yelled as loudly as he could, drowning out the sound of the 3i's voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh!  Ah... We're okay in here!!  Everything is perfectly alright!! ... My friend's just having a little nap, that's all...&quot;<br>
<br>
He paused for a split second to make sure that the 3i had finished its message, then slid to the floor.  That had been horrible!!  Crow stared wildly at the door, then back at Derla.  If that hadn't arisen a few suspicions, he didn't know what would...<br>
<br>
And worst of all, the 3i had confirmed their deepest fears.  Kuro was near... And he had them right where he wanted them.<br>
<br>
Wake up, Derla... Crow thought numbly, staring at her pale face.  We're in trouble now...<br>
