<br>
Crow sat on the dusty floor, almost unable to believe how bad their situation had just gotten.  <br>
<br>
If it weren't for Derla being unconscious, we'd be out of here...<br>
<br>
Looking around the room. Crow contemplated the idea of just hauling Derla out of the hotel and running away.  But he discarded that idea as being pointless and dangerous; Kurt, or Kuro, or whoever that guy was, probably wouldn't let them escape in a hurry.<br>
<br>
...I shouldn't have let her do this... Was healing the 3i worth it?  I mean... <br>
<br>
His thoughts sprawled aimlessly across his mind, Crow wanted to lie down and join Derla in her haunted slumber.  But that would have been suicide.<br>
<br>
Forced to wait, crouched by Derla's side and hoping and praying that she would just wake up, Crow felt a trace of helplessness seeping into his otherwise somewhat reckless spirit.  He sighed, combing his fingers through his hair as he often did when he was agitated, and watched Derla sleep.<br>
<br>
This is torture... I could be out of here, but I can't leave Derla alone!  I'm stuck, and she's stuck.  The perfect trap.<br>
<br>
Crow stared at the door, waiting, and watching for any signs of an attack.<br>
<br>
If you don't wake up in half and hour, Derla... then....<br>
<br>
Crow slumped, the 3i still sending an occasional crackle of pain through his skull.<br>
<br>
Then I don't know what I'll do... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrifairy05>KerriFairy05</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/2/03 4:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is not good</span><hr size=1> Derla could feel herself stirring very gently... 'Finally! I have to wake up... NOW!!!&quot;' She forced herself somewhere between Coniousness and Unconiousness. &quot;Wake up Wake up, stupid body! My mind and spirit are awake.. why isn't my body? Wake uuuuupppp!&quot; Suddenly she was sitting up in a cold sweat, Crow leaning down beside her. &quot;We have to get out of here!&quot; was the first thing that came out of her mouth. She jumped up and was almost out the door when Kurt poked his head in the door.<br>
