Kage held the rag tenderly. 'Do you value her? Cuz if you do, you'll back off...' He put his hand on Derla's shoulder. &quot;It's not far, It's called the El Chico or something.&quot; He began leading her away. <br>
<br>
&quot;Um.. really? That's interesting... Crow?&quot; She turned her head so that Kurt couldn't see her face and silently screamed for help. She was about to ask him if that's where he wanted to go to cover her silent plea, when Kurt's hand snapped around her face, a rag covered her mouth and hand, and she started to scream.<br>
<br>
&quot;Calme down, wench! I'm not gonna hurt you.. as long as Junior over there keeps his piece.&quot; He looked at Crow. His disguise had disappeared and he was now Kage. &quot;Isn't it amazign how I know that you won't attack...&quot; he held Derla, who was holding her breath, infront of him, &quot;If the girl becomes a shield?&quot; He began backing up the steps to the attic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=animagess@collisionworld>Animagess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/2/03 4:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is not good</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
Crow's eyes widened as Kage began dragging Derla out into the corridor.  &quot;Hey... Hey!!&quot;  He began advancing towards the pair, taking out the synteshart; but slowly, as he didn't want Kage hurting Derla if he came too close.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well well, Kage,&quot; said Crow, somehow managing to keep his head.  The 3i was flaring brightly, but since it was already obvious that they were in danger, it was silent.  &quot;It may be true that I won't attack you for fear of hurting Derla... But will YOU risk hurting her?&quot;  Crow took a step for every one that Kage took backwards.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't know what you want with her... But I'm sure you haven't come this far just to kill her,&quot; Crow added, taking another step forwards.  &quot;Isn't that right?&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrifairy05>KerriFairy05</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/2/03 4:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is not good</span><hr size=1> Kage smirked. &quot;No, you're right... I wouldn't kill her...&quot; he pulled out his sword. &quot;But I don't have to kill her to hurt her, do I? After all, there are somethings so much worse than death.&quot; He put the knife to her shoulder and acted like he was making a slice. &quot;Right there, and&quot; he made a fake slice on her other arm. &quot;there and... well you get the idea...&quot; he had he around the middle and was proceeding to the stairs.<br>
<br>
Derla was turning blue. She took a deep slow breath when he removed the rag. She stayed silent, knowing that to say anything would be fatal to Crow. She looked at him as her heels drug the floor. Kage then licked the side of her face and she bit back a scream.<br>
<br>
&quot;So many things worse than death.... mwheheheh..&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#060C65><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bcollisionworld.showUserPublicProfile?gid=animagess@collisionworld>Animagess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(3/2/03 5:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fcollisionworldfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: This is not good</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
Crow stopped in his tracks, breathing hard.  &quot;Ha ha... Heh... Kage, you sick little...&quot;  He stared into Derla's frightened eyes, and then at the monster dragging her up the stairs.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dispensing with the usual witty hero-type bluffs, there's not much I can say, Kage...&quot; Crow breathed, gripping the synteshart hard in one hand.  &quot;Nothing I can say for now.&quot;<br>
<br>
He couldn't do anything except watch with brightened eyes as Kage disappeared with Derla into the attic; Crow no longer needed to check to see what was there, for the answer lay in the stench of the air and the gold words from the 3i.<br>
<br>
As soon as he heard the sounds of someone jumping out the window, he turned and ran back downstairs.  He opened the door and rushed outside just in time to see a shadowy figure and its burden leaping away across the rooftops.<br>
<br>
Tingling with the strangeness of it, Crow started forward, determined not to let them get out of his sight...<br>
